
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `delv` baraye hazf kardan yek version az go estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad version-haye go ke digar niaz nadarid ra az system khod hazf konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `delv list` --> 📜 List kardan hameye version-haye nasb shode Go.
    🔹 `delv <version>` --> 🔥 Hazf kardan yek version moshakhas az Go (masalan, `delv 1.16`).
    🔹 `delv help` --> ❓ Namayesh dastoor-e rahnama baraye `delv`.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ delv list

    🔹 List kardan hameye version-haye nasb shode Go.

    $ delv 1.17

    🔹 Hazf kardan version 1.17 az Go.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ delv list
    go1.16
    go1.17
    go1.18
    $ delv 1.17
    Removing go1.17...
    Done.
    $ delv list
    go1.16
    go1.18

    🔹 Avval hameye version-ha list mishavand, sepas version 1.17 hazf shode va dobare list mishavad ta natije namayesh dade shavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `delv` command is used to remove a Go version. It helps you uninstall Go versions that are no longer needed from your system.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `delv list` --> 📜 List all installed Go versions.
    🔹 `delv <version>` --> 🔥 Remove a specific Go version (e.g., `delv 1.16`).
    🔹 `delv help` --> ❓ Display help information for `delv`.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ delv list

    🔹 List all installed Go versions.

    $ delv 1.17

    🔹 Remove Go version 1.17.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ delv list
    go1.16
    go1.17
    go1.18
    $ delv 1.17
    Removing go1.17...
    Done.
    $ delv list
    go1.16
    go1.18

    🔹 First, all installed versions are listed, then version 1.17 is removed, and the list is displayed again to show the result.
